{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"300j–27","heading":"Registry for lead exposure and Advisory Committee","label":"300j–27 Registry for lead exposure and Advisory Committee","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300j–27","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch6A/schXII/ptF","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs300j%E2%80%9327","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Federal Advisory Committee Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(4), is , , , which was set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and was substantially repealed and restated in chapter 10 (§ 1001 et seq.) of Title 5 by , §§ 3(a), 7, , , 4361. For disposition of sections of the Act into chapter 10 of Title 5, see Disposition Table preceding .Pub. L. 92–46386 Stat. 770Pub. L. 117–286136 Stat. 4197section 101 of Title 5Oct. 6, 1972Dec. 27, 2022","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Water and Waste Act of 2016, and also as part of the Water Infrastructure Improvements for the Nation Act, also known as the WIIN Act, and not as part of the Public Health Service Act which comprises this chapter."],"amendments":["References in TextThe Federal Advisory Committee Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(4), is , , , which was set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees, and was substantially repealed and restated in chapter 10 (§ 1001 et seq.) of Title 5 by , §§ 3(a), 7, , , 4361. For disposition of sections of the Act into chapter 10 of Title 5, see Disposition Table preceding .Pub. L. 92–46386 Stat. 770Pub. L. 117–286136 Stat. 4197section 101 of Title 5Oct. 6, 1972Dec. 27, 2022"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300j–27/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300j–27","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs3